			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Any mapper can do 4-screen, but some mappers may require more complicated logic on the cartridge than others. On discrete logic mappers with CHR-RAM, the use of 4-screen is trivial: one wire on the cartridge tells the NES to keep its internal VRAM permanently off so the VRAM in the cartridge (which must be at least 16KB) is used not only for attribute tables, but also for name tables.<br /><br />GTROM is cool and takes things a step further, doubling the CHR-RAM and NT capacity through bankswitching.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
