					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I find it interesting to observe that besides Tengen's Gauntlet and Irem's Napoleon Senki (and Rad Racer 2, which doesn't seem to use it for actual four-way scrolling), the only other games that use 4-screen VRAM (and that I'm aware of) are Sachen games, namely Jurassic Boy 2, Rocman X and Zhōngguó Dàhēng. Zhōngguó Dàhēng actually uses six nametables --- four on cartridge RAM for the game board, and the two in the console for the status bar.</div>

